HEADWORD: Erd
<hw>Erd</hw> <pr>(⟦etil⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>erd</ets>, <ets>eard</ets>, earth, land, country, AS.
<ets>eard</ets>; akin to OS. <ets>ard</ets> dwelling place, OHG.
<ets>art</ets> plowing, tillage, Icel. <ets>⟦oum⟧r⟦edh⟧</ets> crop, and
to L. <ets>arare</ets> to plow, E. <ets>ear</ets> to plow.]</ety>
<def>The earth.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Wright.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Erd shrew</b></col> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>, <cd>the
common European shrew (<spn>Sorex vulgaris</spn>); the
shrewmouse.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
